---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Link from '../components/Link.astro';
import Lightbox from '../components/Lightbox.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Claims Data API Websites">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 text-slate-900 mt-24">
    <header class="mb-10">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4">Claims Data API Websites</h1>
        <section class="mb-10 bg-gray-100 p-4 border-l-4 border-gray-400">
            <p class="italic text-slate-900">
                Note: This work is public and open-source, but some details about the process have been omitted for confidentiality.
            </p>
        </section>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">
        The Product
    </h2>
      <p>
        <Link text="The Centers for Medicaid and Medicare (CMS)" href="https://www.cms.gov/" /> 
        maintain four FHIR APIs that allow providers, payers,
        and patients to securely access interoperable healthcare claims data: 
        <Link text="AB2D" href="https://ab2d.cms.gov" />,
        <Link text="BCDA" href="https://bcda.cms.gov" />,
        <Link text="DPC" href="https://dpc.cms.gov" />, and
        <Link text="Blue Button" href="https://bluebutton.cms.gov" />.
      </p>

    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Goal</h2>
      <p>
        CMS wanted to identify barriers to adoption and increase the number of organizations using the APIs in production.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">My Role</h2>
      <p>
        I led strategy for this effort and contributed to research, design, and front end development. I worked closely with a talented team of content strategists, product managers, and developers.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10 -mx-4 md:-mx-6 lg:-mx-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-slate-100">
            <a href="/project-images/ab2d-home.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open AB2D home in full size">
              <img src="/project-images/ab2d-home.png" alt="AB2D home" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </figure>

        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-slate-100">
            <a href="/project-images/bb-home.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open Blue Button home in full size">
              <img src="/project-images/bb-home.png" alt="Blue Button home" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </figure>

        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-slate-100">
            <a href="/project-images/bcda-home.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open BCDA home in full size">
              <img src="/project-images/bcda-home.png" alt="BCDA home" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 text-slate-900 mt-0 mb-10">

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2" id="highlights">Highlights</h2>
      
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1 mt-4">
        <li><strong>3 websites</strong> launched in 2025.</li>
        <li>An average of <strong>7,442 unique users</strong> visit the redesigned sites every week.</li>
        <li><strong>33,647,348 beneficiaries served</strong> by these API websites (as of Nov. 2025).</li>
        <li>AB2D experienced a <strong>115% increase of average visitors</strong> per month after launch.</li>
        <li>BCDA experienced a <strong>68% increase of average visitors</strong> per month after launch.</li>
        <li>
          Blue Button became one of the first government sites to leverage Astro
          for a fast, modern front-end framework (to our knowledge).
        </li>
        <li>
          Published <strong>8 revamped use cases</strong> and <strong>1 major <Link text="white paper" href="https://ab2d.cms.gov/mtm-white-paper" /></strong> based on realistic applications identified in user research.
        </li>
        <li>
          CMS now emphasizes open-source, transparency, and developer UX across API documentation and resources.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  <section>
    <div class="h-px my-10 bg-slate-300 w-full"></div>
  </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold my-6">Process</h2>
<!--       <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
        <a href="/project-images/timeline.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
          <img src="/project-images/timeline.png" alt="Timeline" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
        </a>
      </figure> -->
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: User Research</h3>

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Methods</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Exploratory user interviews</li>
        <li>Journey mapping</li>
        <li>Gap analysis</li>
      </ul>

      <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
        <a href="/project-images/journey-map.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
          <img src="/project-images/journey-map.png" alt="Journey map" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
        </a>
        <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
            User journey map across all Bulk FHIR APIs, synthesizing pain points and opportunities identified in user interviews.         
        </p>
      </figure>

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Findings</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Pain points for developer users and non-technical users</li>
        <li>
          Obstacles in the journey to production, including detailed feedback on the high technical barrier to entry
        </li>
        <li>Gaps in API documentation</li>
        <li>Updated value propositions informed by user experience</li>
        <li>
          Use cases for each API, which were later used to publish case studies and white papers.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 bg-orange-100 p-4 border-l-4 border-orange-600">
        <p class="italic text-slate-900 text-lg">
            "It was just an email thread that went around that was like 'Is anybody interested in this? Does anyone have any utilization?' and that's how we got started."
        </p>
        <p class="italic text-slate-900 text-lg pt-2">
            â€” AB2D User
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: Standardization Strategy</h3>
      <p>
        I recommended that we apply research findings to improve the public website and documentation for AB2D, then extend this effort to other APIs. This strategy to standardize emphasized joint research efforts, a repeatable approach, and pre-built web templates that could be used across all four APIs.
      </p>
      <!-- image: current states -->

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Key Strategy Points</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>
            Leveraging <Link text="USWDS" href="https://designsystem.digital.gov/" />
        </li>
        <li>Content-first approach, with focus on developer experience (Dev-X)</li>
        <li>The <Link text="Diataxis" href="https://diataxis.fr/" /> framework</li>
        <li>Rapid prototyping and usability testing</li>
        <li>Universal information architecture and steps to onboard</li>
        <li>Developing maintainable, reusable, user-validated web templates</li>
        <li>
          Enabling all teammates to easily update the websites, even without front-end expertise
        </li>
      </ul>

      <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
        <a href="/project-images/competitive-analysis.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
          <img src="/project-images/competitive-analysis.png" alt="Competitive analysis" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
          <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
            A high-level snapshot of information architecture across similar Dev-X websites reveals competitve industry standards and Diataxis principles.
          </p>
        </a>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: Design</h3>

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Methods</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Current-state analysis</li>
        <li>Card sort</li>
        <li>Competitive analysis</li>
        <li>Usability testing</li>
        <li>Web analytics</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
            <a href="/project-images/card-sort.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open card sort in full size">
            <img src="/project-images/card-sort.png" alt="Card sort" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
            </a>
            <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
                Card sort exercise 
            </p>
        </figure>

        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
            <a href="/project-images/before-web-analytics.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
            <img src="/project-images/before-web-analytics.png" alt="Before web analytics" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
            </a>
            <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
                Web analytics sample 
            </p>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4">
        We spent several sprints mocking up and testing key user flows and improved documentation for a single API, AB2D. We could extend these learnings and to other APIs down the road to save time and to reinforce standardized practices.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4">
        Crucially, we kept in close contact with Product Managers and stakeholders from other APIs throughout prototyping. This ensured that designs were universalized for each API's unique features and user needs.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4">
       In testing, the majority of users sorted 34/36 task flows into the same category/page. This validated the robustness and accuracy of the new information architecture.
      </p>

      <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
            <a href="/project-images/task-flows.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
            <img src="/project-images/task-flows.png" alt="Task flows" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
            </a>
            <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
                Results of testing for key task flows shows agreement among the majority of users.
            </p>
        </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 4: AB2D Implementation</h3>

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Framework</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li><Link text="Ruby + Jekyll + USWDS" href="https://github.com/navapbc/template-jekyll-uswds" /></li>
        <li>Later, Blue Button became one of the first government websites to move to <Link text="Astro" href="astro" /></li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="heading text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold py-3">Approach</h4>

      <p>
        Designs were implemented in a staging environment on a page-by-page basis,
        allowing for simultaneous, agile development.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4">
        We used <Link text="Markdown" href="https://www.markdownguide.org" /> and <Link text="TypeScript" href="https://www.typescriptlang.org" /> to create intuitive code components that extended USWDS within guardrails, allowing non-technical teammates to contribute to code.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
            <a href="/project-images/process-list-design.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open card sort in full size">
            <img src="/project-images/process-list-design.png" alt="Process list design" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
            </a>
            <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
                Design for the process list component
            </p>
        </figure>

        <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
            <a href="/project-images/process-list-code.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open journey map in full size">
            <img src="/project-images/process-list-code.png" alt="Process list code" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
            </a>
            <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
                Code for the process list component 
            </p>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4">
        After all pages had been implemented and user-tested, the full website was publicly launched at <Link text="https://ab2d.cms.gov/" href="https://ab2d.cms.gov/" />.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 5: Standardized Implementation</h3>

      <p class="mt-4">
        Since information architecture, layouts, and front-end templates were already built and validated by users, we were able to skip the design stage altogether and implement new content directly in staging. 
      </p>
        
      <p class="mt-4">
        <strong>We developed the following sites in weeks instead of months, then days instead of weeks.</strong>
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1 mt-4">
        <li>3 websites launched in 2025. Scroll back up to <a class="underline text-orange-700 hover:text-orange-800" href="#highlights">the highlights.</a></li>
        <li>
          Other teams at CMS are using these open-source, standard templates to independently spin up similar websites.
        </li>
        <li>
          Reduction in support requests from users following the release of improved sites and documentation.
        </li>
        <li>
          Nava published a <Link text="Case Study" href="https://www.navapbc.com/case-studies/improving-medicare-coordination-api" /> about this effort in the Annual Public Benfit Report.
        <li>
          Non-technical teammates have been able to successfully update and contribute to the API websites, proving maintainability. One content writer even made <Link text="a blog" href="https://bcda.cms.gov/announcements.html" />.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <figure class="bg-white rounded-md shadow overflow-hidden my-6">
        <a href="/project-images/case-study.png" data-lightbox aria-label="Open case study in full size">
          <img src="/project-images/case-study.png" alt="Case study" class="w-full h-auto object-contain" />
        </a>
        <p class="p-4 text-sm text-slate-900">
            Read the <Link text="Case Study" href="https://www.navapbc.com/case-studies/improving-medicare-coordination-api" />.        
        </p>
      </figure>
    </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
